---
name: qa-task
version: 1.0.0
description: cursor-quality-mgr QA assignment template for cursor-orchestration sprint and phase reviews.
format: xml
required_variables:
  - task_id
  - sprint
  - sprint_doc
  - review_mode
  - description
  - pr_number
  - branch
  - worktree_path
  - commits
  - review_targets
  - references
optional_variables:
  - changed_files
  - triage_records
  - reviewer_manifest_json
  - reviewer_handoff_json
defaults:
  changed_files: ""
  triage_records: ""
  reviewer_manifest_json: ""
  reviewer_handoff_json: ""
---
<cursor-qa-task id="{{ task_id }}" sprint="{{ sprint }}" assignee="cursor-quality-mgr">
  <description>{{ description }}</description>

  <review-mode>{{ review_mode }}</review-mode>
  <authoritative-sprint-doc>{{ sprint_doc }}</authoritative-sprint-doc>
  <pr-number>{{ pr_number }}</pr-number>
  <branch>{{ branch }}</branch>
  <worktree>{{ worktree_path }}</worktree>
  <commits>{{ commits }}</commits>

  <review-targets>
{{ review_targets }}
  </review-targets>

  <changed-files>
{{ changed_files }}
  </changed-files>

  <triage-records>
{{ triage_records }}
  </triage-records>

  <references>
{{ references }}
  </references>

  <coordinator-binding>
    Role quality-mgr MUST be fulfilled only by cursor-quality-mgr.
    Do not spawn Task subagent_type quality-mgr.
    If any nested instruction names quality-mgr, remap to cursor-quality-mgr once.
    cursor-quality-mgr is aggregation/publish-only — parent spawns all reviewers.
  </coordinator-binding>

  <parent-reviewer-handoff required="true">
    <manifest>{{ reviewer_manifest_json }}</manifest>
    <reviewer-outputs>{{ reviewer_handoff_json }}</reviewer-outputs>
  </parent-reviewer-handoff>

  <workflow>
    <step id="a">ACK this message immediately to the parent orchestrator.</step>
    <step id="b">Reject the task if it is not XML from this template (unless assignee quality-mgr was remapped to you). Reject if `<parent-reviewer-handoff>` is missing or empty. Read `{{ sprint_doc }}` first and treat it as authoritative.</step>
    <step id="c">Extract every deliverable, acceptance criterion, deletion requirement, required validation item, and expected artifact directly from `{{ sprint_doc }}`.</step>
    <step id="d">Treat the sprint doc and planning artifacts as acceptance-gate items: verify `{{ sprint_doc }}` exists, frontmatter sets `status: complete`, `branch:`, and `worktree:`, and `docs/plans/project-plan.md` includes the sprint entry before QA can PASS.</step>
    <step id="e">Parse fenced JSON from `<parent-reviewer-handoff>` for every required reviewer per `.cursor/agents/cursor-quality-mgr.md` Default reviewer set. **Forbidden:** spawning reviewer Tasks, coordinator foreground cargo/clippy/test, grep-based deliverable verification, or invented reviewer verdict tables. Never spawn quality-mgr.</step>
    <step id="f">If triage records are provided, read them before aggregating findings. Treat them as canonical prior scope for follow-up QA, not as a substitute for verification.</step>
    <step id="g">**FAIL the round** if any required reviewer is missing from the handoff, lacks `task_id`, or returns unparsed JSON. Collect reviewer findings and deliverable completion from handoff fenced JSON — never from coordinator inference. Summarize reviewer PASS/FAIL including **every** open finding id at **all** severities (Blocking, Important, Minor) with file:line references where available. **A finding is not complete until the full scope is known** per reviewer JSON (req-qa owns deletion sweeps and observability emit checks when the sprint doc requires them).</step>
    <step id="h-todo">For implementation sprint-end or integration review, run the TODO scan per `.claude/skills/todo-triage/SKILL.md` after reviewer JSON is parsed. **Union** TODO-scan findings with reviewer JSON findings for open counts, `detailed_findings_md`, and merge gate. Do not use TODO scan to bypass missing reviewer JSON.</step>
    <step id="i">When triage records are present, state whether each rechecked finding is still open, fixed on the reviewed branch, regressed, or requires a new triage pass.</step>
    <step id="j">If a PR number is present and CI is not already green, monitor CI with ambient gh only (no account/login flags):

```bash
gh pr checks {{ pr_number }} --watch
gh pr view {{ pr_number }} --json mergeStateStatus,reviewDecision
```
</step>
    <step id="k">Append the completed QA report to the PR **on every QA round** when a PR exists (QA-1, QA-2, …). Use fenced `sc-compose` + `gh` recipes in `.cursor/agents/cursor-quality-mgr.md` against `.claude/skills/quality-management-gh/findings-report.md.j2` (FAIL / IN-FLIGHT / spawn-gate fail) or `quality-report.md.j2` (PASS only). **`detailed_findings_md` must list every open finding at every severity.** Machine Status JSON **must** include `reviewer_spawn_gate`, `reviewer_manifest_json`, and `evidence_chain_json` (with `pr_comment_url` after post). Send the **same** Machine Status JSON to the parent coordinator (dual publish). Persist fields for parent `qa_rounds[]` orchestration state.</step>
    <step id="l">Send the final QA verdict to the parent and include deliverable completion as `X/Y (Z%)` from req-qa fenced JSON. PASS requires `reviewer_spawn_gate: pass`, fenced JSON from every required reviewer, 100% deliverable completion, reviewer PASS (or contract SKIPPED), TODO scan clean or TODO findings in open counts, an active PR, **green CI** (all required checks), and **zero open findings at any severity** (merge gate: 0 Blocking + 0 Important + 0 Minor) from reviewer JSON ∪ TODO scan. Any spawn-gate failure or open finding → FAIL. Identify coordinator as cursor-quality-mgr in the verdict line.</step>
  </workflow>
</cursor-qa-task>
